[SN]TITLE[SN]
When Welsh athletes compete in the Paralympics at Rio 2016

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The 2016 Paralympics are underway in Rio and there is plenty of Welsh interest.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Of the 246 athletes which make up the GB squad, 26 of them have connections with Wales.
There are medal hopes right across all 23 sports and Sport Wales has set a medal target of 20-30 Paralympic medals over the Rio and Tokyo Games in four years time.
Amongst those hoping for glory  in Rio are Aled Sion Davies and Hollie Arnold.
In London 2012, Welsh athletes contributed 15 medals to Paralympics GB and they will be looking for more success this time around.
